        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 12 at 3:21PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 321 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Alamosa, moving northeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Alamosa, Mosca, and San Luis Lake.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
